# Phase 1 (Bug AL) seed: fastjson2 JdbcSupport$TimeReader.readObject reuses JVM slot 5 for THREE
# disjoint live ranges (a long unix-time, a DateTimeFormatter, a String). Each range's bare
# declaration must be hoisted to the method top with its CORRECT type so every use is in scope and
# type-checks (the original bug rendered the second range out of scope -> "cannot find symbol:
# variable var5_1"). The live-interval declaration placement (JDEC_LIVEINTERVAL_OFF) hoists the bare
# declarations to the method top, dominating all uses.
#
# Note: this golden originally pinned only `+long var5_1;`. A later disjoint-range numbering change
# renamed the long range to var5 and assigned var5_1/var5_2 to the DateTimeFormatter/String ranges.
# The real JdbcSupport$TimeReader compiles CLEAN in the authoritative whole-jar (tree) recompile, so
# the output is correct -- the golden is updated to assert all three typed hoisted declarations, a
# strictly stronger invariant than the single original rule.
+long var5;
+DateTimeFormatter var5_1;
+String var5_2;
